cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.SD

The paper discusses the development of an adaptive structure learning method for Restricted Boltzmann Machine (RBM) and Deep Belief Network (DBN) for classification tasks. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also mentions the use of the CIFAR-10 dataset, which is commonly used in computer vision tasks, indicating a possible sub-category of computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper discusses the incorporation of knowledge into the classification algorithm, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and knowledge representation and reasoning (cs.SD).
